<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Impious" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Impious,</orth> sinful, wicked: <bibl n="shak. luc 199" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 199</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 199" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 199</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 105</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 3, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.1.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 1, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.53" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.2.94" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 2, 94</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 3, 17</bibl> (M. Edd. <emph>pious</emph>). Irreverence to God, the primary meaning, distinctly traceable in <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 6</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>